## Key Takeaways

- The transmitter successfully upconverts a **10 MHz baseband signal to 2.435 GHz**
- All blocks pass post-layout verification with acceptable performance degradation
- Total power consumption of **8.925 mW** makes it suitable for battery-operated BLE devices
- Efficiency of **22.7%** is reasonable for a Class A architecture at this power level
- Design is compliant with BLE frequency band requirements (2400–2483.5 MHz)

